Finally, Model 3 can be used to estimate the unobserved number of exposed, E(t), and infectious, I(t), cases during the development of the pandemic. The maximum number of exposed cases occurs on the 21st of March 2020 and is estimated to be 173 cases, Fig. 4 (right, blue line), with the maximum of infectious individuals (136) being attained on the 26th of March 2020. We can observe a delay in the transition of exposed to infectious in the order of 5 days, which suggests a 5 day latent time of COVID-19.Figure 4
